<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1263502 size-large" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=640%2C420&#038;ssl=1" alt="8 die, another 8 test positive to Yellow fever in Bauchi" width="640" height="420" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=1024%2C672&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=300%2C197&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=768%2C504&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=58%2C38&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=260%2C171&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=198%2C130&amp;ssl=1 198w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?resize=560%2C367&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/yellow-fever.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Bauchi State Primary Healthcare Development Agency (BSPHCDA) says that an outbreak of yellow fever has occurred in Ganjuwa Local Government Areas (LGA) of Bauchi State with eight deaths and eight samples testing positive. The Chairman of the agency, Dr Rilwanu Mohammed, stated this while briefing newsmen in Bauch on Monday. “Our polio team were in communities in Ganjuwa for  routine exercise and they found out that eight people died of unknown disease, so they reported back. “Eight samples were brought for lassa fever and yellow fever  tests and all the samples tested positive for yellow fever. “Last year, by this time, we had cases of yellow fever in six LGA of Bauchi, Alkaleri, Warji, Ningi, Kirfi and Darazo,” he said. The chairman said that the community members were predominantly farmers. Mohammed said that the agency would begin vaccination exercise in earnest against the deadly disease in Ganjuwa LGA. Mohammed called on the general public not to panic as yellow fever has a vaccine. He also advised the public on the use of mosquito nets as a preventive measure against other types of fever. Vanguard News Nigeria Dr Rilwanu Mohammed, Chairman, Bauchi State Primary Healthcare Development Agency (BSPHDA), said on Thursday that 29 people had died from an outbreak of yellow fever in the state. November 7, 2019 In "Health" By Chioma Obinna The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, and the National Primary Health Care Development Agency, NPHCDA, yesterday announced the laboratory confirmation of 15 cases of yellow fever from the 169 clinically suspected cases recorded in Bauchi between August 29th and 11th of September, 2019. In a press… September 20, 2019 In "Health" The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, and the National Primary Health Care Development Agency, NPHCDA, yesterday announced the laboratory confirmation of 15 cases of yellow fever from the 169 clinically suspected cases recorded in Bauchi between August 29th and 11th of September, 2019. September 19, 2019 In "Health"